euweb forum software
https://rapideuphoria.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/rapideuphoria/tools/euweb/trunk

Dependencies:
=======================

edbi       http://jeremy.cowgar.com/svn/edbi/trunk
webclay2   http://jeremy.cowgar.com/svn/webclay2/trunk

The edbi and webclay2 files are included like:

    include edbi/edbi.e
    include webclay/webclay.e as wc

Therefore, they should be put into a directory called "edbi" or
"webclay", respectively that is a subdirectory of a directory 
in the include path (configurable via eu.cfg file, -i flags 
on the command line or EUDIR) or of the euweb source directory.


config.e
=======================

Read source/config.e.  Create your own configuration file and include it from
source/config.e inside an ifdef.  A sample config file might look like:

        public constant DB_DRIVERS_PATH = "drivers"
        public constant DB_URL = "mysql://user:password@localhost:3306/database_name"

        -- Do NOT include the trailing slash
        public constant ROOT_URL = "http://localhost"

        public constant AUTO_LOGIN_UID = 0 -- 0 disables, otherwise set to your UID

        -- reCAPTCHA keys
        public constant RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY = ""
        public constant RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY = ""


Database
=========================

euweb uses a MySQL database, so you'll need to have the MySQL server installed.


Configuring Apache
=======================
euweb uses some rewrite rules to make some friendly urls, but 
it uses an htaccess also.

	Options +ExecCGI
	RewriteEngine on

	#IP_BAN_LIST
	#RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} ^189\.84\.117\.2 [OR]
	#RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} ^96\.246\.214\.212 [OR]
	#RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} ^200\.215\.15\.10 [OR]
	#RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} ^96\.224\.139\.195 [OR]
	#RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} ^71\.190\.5\.103
	#RewriteRule .* - [F]

	#RewriteRule (.*) updating.html
	#RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^oe\.cowgar\.com
	#RewriteRule (.*)$ http://oe.cowgar.com/$1  [L,R=301]

	RewriteRule ^docs/$ /docs/eu400_0001.html
	RewriteRule ^user/profile/(.+)\.wc$
	/euweb.cgi?module=user&action=profile&user=$1 [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^forum/m/([0-9]+)\.wc$
	/euweb.cgi?module=forum&action=message&id=$1 [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^([^\.]+)/([0-9]+)\.wc$
	/euweb.cgi?module=$1&action=view&id=$2 [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^(.+)/([^\.]+)\.wc$ /euweb.cgi?module=$1&action=$2 [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^([^\.]+)\.wc$ /euweb.cgi?module=$1&action=index [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^([^\.]+)/$ /euweb.cgi?module=$1&action=index [L,QSA]
	RewriteRule ^$ /euweb.cgi?module=index&action=index [L,QSA]

	<Files ~ "^\.htaccess">
	Order allow,deny
	Deny from all
	</Files>

	<Files ~ "^eu\.cfg">
	Order allow,deny
	Deny from all
	</Files>
